<subSubSection id="C84050F55EC50FF4B0D81FD5A20E863C" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" type="notes">
<paragraph id="EEAA00C2C165911395957BA2CA249799" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="107E3A79EBFB6C2AFFEF93315676A1F3" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">
<normalizedToken id="26D22664B041BC2BC198F155A386EF18" originalValue="Mènètriès">Menetries</normalizedToken>
(1832) describes 
<taxonomicName id="965786826CFD431A9D48622BB175E85A" authorityName="Neri &amp; Toledano" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Neri &amp; Toledano" baseAuthorityYear="1832" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion (Peryphus) dimidiatum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dimidiatum" subGenus="Peryphus">Bembidion (Peryphus) dimidiatum</taxonomicName>
from the banks of 
<normalizedToken id="4278CDA6243CCB8F17436213C6CA7A5E" originalValue="“Potkoumà”">&quot;Potkouma&quot;</normalizedToken>
near 
<normalizedToken id="F497FDF6E8AE126204BAB1255AD0CC25" originalValue="“Pétigorsk”">&quot;Petigorsk&quot;</normalizedToken>
on &quot;quelques individus&quot;. After the description, 
<taxonomicName id="8630E2989CBECC7B64C62BCD621E65AA" genus="B." lsidName="B. dimidiatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="dimidiatum">
<emphasis id="7313DC606DAA7026293D2BCACD08C9E9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. dimidiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was retained as strictly related to 
<taxonomicName id="4FB77F1355721664A2C08316E7E682EF" genus="B." lsidName="B. oblongum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="oblongum">
<emphasis id="6DDA5814986F5C0AC69BCD2B495FC52D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. oblongum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1831 or 
<taxonomicName id="570D5FF5A67FBEEC344CC7893BAB4B96" genus="B." lsidName="B. ripicola" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="ripicola">
<emphasis id="21B16B135C3151B8412A11AC710A9288" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. ripicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dufour, 1820 (currently all species belonging to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="3108283CF998850CAB12D8BAA8384D8B" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion (Euperyphus)" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Euperyphus">Bembidion Euperyphus</taxonomicName>
Jeannel, 1941). 
<bibRefCitation id="7644543B163F721E3ACFE3AF68939196" author="Netolitzky, F" journalOrPublisher="Wiener Entomologische Zeitung" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" refId="B41" refString="Netolitzky, F, 1914a. Die Bembidiini in Winklers Catalogus. Entomologische Blatter 10(1/2): 50-55." title="Die Bembidiini in Winklers Catalogus. Entomologische Blatter 10 (1 / 2): 50 - 55." year="1914 a">Netolitzky (1914a)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName id="29BC008CFA537D6C2CE774DAA981FAAF" genus="B." lsidName="B. dimidiatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="dimidiatum">
<emphasis id="1C406535926844B2D97EB2D0DF2D9B80" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. dimidiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="458DD8A6507529E86F6C2B976F9004B6" genus="B." lsidName="B. tricolor" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="tricolor">
<emphasis id="812C90C449CC6912DA3A836B25B4DEF3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. tricolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fabricius, 1801) (= 
<taxonomicName id="24A00A22C7CC0363E535DEACBBF9E3DC" genus="B." lsidName="B. varicolor" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="varicolor">
<emphasis id="4390BE26F5AB803AE258A808DF8FF83F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. varicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fabricius, 1803); the synonymy derives from the fact that the author examined Caucasian specimens identified as 
<taxonomicName id="8C4966FC1B9C9098518418F20D2B0C3D" genus="B." lsidName="B. dimidiatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="dimidiatum">
<emphasis id="1EA8656EE0FB36C835D4241C19ED1313" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. dimidiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
actually belonging to 
<taxonomicName id="1FA658DC1F127DD38831521281D50103" genus="B." lsidName="B. (Bembidionetolitzkya) varicolor" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="varicolor" subGenus="Bembidionetolitzkya">B. (Bembidionetolitzkya) varicolor</taxonomicName>
and was perhaps unaware that this last species also occurs in the Caucasus and shares the same particular pattern of color of the European 
<taxonomicName id="7866644E58981FB51EA86090BF80EB98" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion varicolor" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varicolor">
<emphasis id="89366F37EFF9EDD6561F993D7BA1A10A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">Bembidion varicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. But later (1935) the author himself retained 
<taxonomicName id="33868A2111E20D2C2690EC60616DC6A7" genus="B." lsidName="B. dimidiatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="dimidiatum">
<emphasis id="9FFE6328B5BAE69AB81CA8DADB67D41A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. dimidiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="A31A9C3A940848CB15E661C6F41D57B0" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1831" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion oblongum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oblongum">
<emphasis id="E0236794FAB8EC1F2E14B806BE727EA4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">Bembidion oblongum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and in any case not similar to 
<taxonomicName id="74057097D84E815EB8C5E4BF7917BC68" genus="B." lsidName="B. conforme" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="conforme">
<emphasis id="1BCAF0F408FCC086E4064ABA05B01721" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. conforme</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1831 or 
<taxonomicName id="B1F9CC001BB3E503424B5E61DBFD7C04" genus="B." lsidName="B. tricolor" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="tricolor">
<emphasis id="029633B3928BBAFFEFA5FBC1F126419E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. tricolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(both belonging to subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="9231D783EAB5DBAC06F8CBB75C60F844" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion (Bembidionetolitzkya)" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Bembidionetolitzkya">Bembidion Bembidionetolitzkya</taxonomicName>
Strand, 1929). 
<bibRefCitation id="EE6785CF407FEA2E732545CF3FF6D44F" author="Netolitzky, F" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Royal Entomological Society of London - Series B: Taxonomy" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" refId="B45" refString="Netolitzky, F, 1943a. Bestimmungs-Tabellen europaeischer Kaefer (9. Stück). II. Fam. Carabidae. Subfam. Bembidiinae. 66. Gattung: Bembidion Latr. Bestimmungstabelle der Bembidion-Arten des palaearktischen Gebietes. (Mit Hinweisen auf holarktische, aethiopische und orientalische Arten). Koleopterologische Rundschau 28(4/6): 69/41-124/96." title="Bestimmungs-Tabellen europaeischer Kaefer (9. Stu ̈ ck). II. Fam. Carabidae. Subfam. Bembidiinae. 66. Gattung: Bembidion Latr. Bestimmungstabelle der Bembidion-Arten des palaearktischen Gebietes. (Mit Hinweisen auf holarktische, aethiopische und orientalische Arten). Koleopterologische Rundschau 28 (4 / 6): 69 / 41 - 124 / 96." year="1943 a">Netolitzky (1943a</bibRefCitation>
: 112/84, note 83) reported that 
<taxonomicName id="7F3745C100CBAA6DE72911E251C983EF" genus="B." lsidName="B. dimidiatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="dimidiatum">
<emphasis id="EFCA5FBC50661C912FFF75011BE7C0E3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. dimidiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the &quot;Gruppe des 
<taxonomicName id="61A4EA1DC22AD66BD8C4C681F1BA3933" genus="B." lsidName="B. ripicola" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="ripicola">
<emphasis id="2A94C8B1C97F7F7AE95344C5FBAD6F7D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. ripicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- 
<taxonomicName id="81E4D3C15A26E13C2C5288BF001463DE" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1831" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion oblongum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oblongum">
<emphasis id="674FDA100F1D58E94BC9F8E9DE85F5CE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">Bembidion oblongum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; and retained it as close to 
<taxonomicName id="A6F6DA8373DAC4FAF1454EA1816BAB6D" genus="B." lsidName="B. testaceum subsp. parallelipenne" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="subSpecies" species="testaceum" subSpecies="parallelipenne">
<emphasis id="F4C5AE350AF657FBA51323067E90BFD7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. testaceum parallelipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Chaudoir, 1850; moreover, 
<bibRefCitation id="762FDBA2C68559060A5C37A3C79DE298" author="Netolitzky, F" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Royal Entomological Society of London - Series B: Taxonomy" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" refId="B46" refString="Netolitzky, F, 1943b. Bestimmungs-Tabellen europaeischer Kaefer (9. Stueck). II. Fam. Carabidae, Subfam. Bembidiinae. 66. Gattung: Bembidion Latr. Bestimmungstabelle der Bembidion-Arten des palaearktischen Gebietes. (Mit Hinweisen auf holarktische, aethiopische und orientalische Arten). Koleopterologische Rundschau 29: 1/97-70/166." title="Bestimmungs-Tabellen europaeischer Kaefer (9. Stueck). II. Fam. Carabidae, Subfam. Bembidiinae. 66. Gattung: Bembidion Latr. Bestimmungstabelle der Bembidion-Arten des palaearktischen Gebietes. (Mit Hinweisen auf holarktische, aethiopische und orientalische Arten). Koleopterologische Rundschau 29: 1 / 97 - 70 / 166." year="1943 b">Netolitzky (1943b</bibRefCitation>
: 17/113, note 18) mentioned that, if they were synonyms, 
<taxonomicName id="4DCD692A6308AFB767615AE9EDC7AB6B" genus="B." lsidName="B. dimidiatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="dimidiatum">
<emphasis id="5C6963128C589F1B7D437BD530358178" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. dimidiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should have priority over 
<taxonomicName id="070989BAA3F5E17CC761BB33ABB3E0A8" genus="B." lsidName="B. parallelipenne" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="parallelipenne">
<emphasis id="9272829BCC9E9EEED711BDEA2194F51C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. parallelipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; he did not formally state in any way this synonymy. Later, Kryzhanovskij et al. (1995) and 
<bibRefCitation id="490FAC7A974987C991BE0A9F27586FE2" author="Lorenz, W" journalOrPublisher="Brill, Leiden-Boston" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" refId="B25" refString="Lorenz, W, 1998. Systematic List of Extant Ground Beetles of the World. Tutzing, 503 pp." title="Systematic List of Extant Ground Beetles of the World. Tutzing, 503 pp." year="1998">Lorenz (1998)</bibRefCitation>
listed 
<taxonomicName id="29B8F7D0FCDD9DC4823A04034A4D36E5" genus="B." lsidName="B. dimidiatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="dimidiatum">
<emphasis id="35595B388FD1186CAA9B4FEAB41D0222" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. dimidiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="F1CA8C34800D2F5A4BB97C6ED17B12C3" genus="B." lsidName="B. parallelipenne" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="parallelipenne">
<emphasis id="EDC6FF26FA7FEA6975AA8B0776A2BEC1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. parallelipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but expressed doubts. 
<bibRefCitation id="0FF7CD8287F7BE392857155E222A6113" author="Marggi, W" journalOrPublisher="Apollo Books, Stenstrup" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" refId="B28" refString="Marggi, W, Huber, C, Mueller-Motzfeld, G, Hartmann, M, 2003. Carabidae: Bembidiini: Bembidiina: 242-273. In: Loebl I, Smetana A (Eds) Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera (Vol. 1). Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga. Apollo Books, Stenstrup" title="Carabidae: Bembidiini: Bembidiina: 242 - 273. In: Loebl I, Smetana A (Eds) Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera (Vol. 1). Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga." year="2003">Marggi et al. (2003</bibRefCitation>
: 271) completely changed direction, moving 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A735707227549659914E471884EC9" authorityName="Neri &amp; Toledano" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Neri &amp; Toledano" baseAuthorityYear="1832" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion dimidiatum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dimidiatum">
<emphasis id="80B3FBD1F7C4316995DB4F24732F6639" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">Bembidion dimidiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to &quot;incertae sedis&quot;, explaining the decision as follows: &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="FDC5D5B7EABAAEF8BE184F16AD335843" authorityName="Chaudoir" authorityYear="1850" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion (Peryphus) parallelipenne" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parallelipenne" subGenus="Peryphus">Bembidion (Peryphus) parallelipenne</taxonomicName>
? syn. 
<taxonomicName id="539567C7906DE8ED4725F1E42E966BB3" authorityName="Neri &amp; Toledano" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Neri &amp; Toledano" baseAuthorityYear="1832" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion dimidiatum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dimidiatum">
<emphasis id="226EAA7A5ECBE0FA2FD9EEBE7C344271" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">Bembidion dimidiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="52EDE136C585776BE892B1CE9A921A42" originalValue="Ménétriés">Menetries</normalizedToken>
, 1832, resurrected as 
<taxonomicName id="AC5CA319AFF422341F7E9635374560DD" authorityName="Neri &amp; Toledano" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Neri &amp; Toledano" baseAuthorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FFB8F086EF485B3BC015D01745308274" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">Bembidion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(incertae sedis) 
<taxonomicName id="ACCE1D7F744DF64881F4D9965FEAD8A3" authorityName="Neri &amp; Toledano" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Neri &amp; Toledano" baseAuthorityYear="1832" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion dimidiatum" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dimidiatum">
<emphasis id="C9C70C439BCB9034CAC0FC4B0A113A5B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">Bembidion dimidiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="A5CC850BE45421EC1BD82A659D62436B" originalValue="Ménétriés">Menetries</normalizedToken>
, 1832. It is not a member of 
<taxonomicName id="5E7A7499BB0DF65A94735024C25BD38B" authorityName="Motschoulsky" authorityYear="1864" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Actedium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Actedium" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E3784F373A5F32FC438E322160963B76" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">Actedium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as given in Lorenz, 1998&quot; (
<bibRefCitation id="D8AB70935A3A99AFC2F1E9445C0B36A8" author="Marggi, W" journalOrPublisher="Apollo Books, Stenstrup" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" refId="B28" refString="Marggi, W, Huber, C, Mueller-Motzfeld, G, Hartmann, M, 2003. Carabidae: Bembidiini: Bembidiina: 242-273. In: Loebl I, Smetana A (Eds) Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera (Vol. 1). Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga. Apollo Books, Stenstrup" title="Carabidae: Bembidiini: Bembidiina: 242 - 273. In: Loebl I, Smetana A (Eds) Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera (Vol. 1). Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga." year="2003">Marggi et al. 2003</bibRefCitation>
: 21).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="205AC0B2AF1BFE719071B2EAE353C46F" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">
The same settlement is confirmed by 
<bibRefCitation id="67AC09EECF28EF416905761B4D24C875" author="Lorenz, W" journalOrPublisher="Brill, Leiden-Boston" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" refId="B26" refString="Lorenz, W, 2005. Systematic List of Extant Ground Beetles of the World (2nd edn.). Tutzing, 530 pp." title="Systematic List of Extant Ground Beetles of the World (2 nd edn.). Tutzing, 530 pp." year="2005">Lorenz (2005)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="638D232BC8B60DA8527D09D60961CDD3" author="Marggi, W" journalOrPublisher="Brill, Leiden" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" refId="B29" refString="Marggi, W, Toledano, L, Neri, P, 2017. Carabidae: Bembidiini: Bembidiina: 294-342. In: Loebl I, Loebl D (Eds) Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera (Vol. I). Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga. Brill, Leiden" title="Carabidae: Bembidiini: Bembidiina: 294 - 342. In: Loebl I, Loebl D (Eds) Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera (Vol. I). Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga." year="2017">Marggi et al. (2017)</bibRefCitation>
. Unfortunately, the sentence of 
<bibRefCitation id="8580E130F27C4581CBD21C96B4F7C9B1" author="Marggi, W" journalOrPublisher="Apollo Books, Stenstrup" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" refId="B28" refString="Marggi, W, Huber, C, Mueller-Motzfeld, G, Hartmann, M, 2003. Carabidae: Bembidiini: Bembidiina: 242-273. In: Loebl I, Smetana A (Eds) Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera (Vol. 1). Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga. Apollo Books, Stenstrup" title="Carabidae: Bembidiini: Bembidiina: 242 - 273. In: Loebl I, Smetana A (Eds) Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera (Vol. 1). Archostemata - Myxophaga - Adephaga." year="2003">Marggi et al. (2003)</bibRefCitation>
above and in particular the reference to 
<taxonomicName id="A2F87AE054FDE54A03332F3C3900D8F0" authorityName="Motschoulsky" authorityYear="1864" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Actedium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Actedium" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="55A62D037876BE45D60933D7CD9D6177" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">Actedium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
probably caused the moving of 
<taxonomicName id="89436BCC618E78618B2CF2C6CF9EE8B9" genus="B." lsidName="B. dimidiatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="dimidiatum">
<emphasis id="11C5B02DA24EDF4400570D97C918F677" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. dimidiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to &quot;incertae sedis&quot;, and are unclear; we verified that in 
<bibRefCitation id="DA0B5D6974B47E2C422B9F898DB6FEC7" author="Lorenz, W" journalOrPublisher="Brill, Leiden-Boston" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" refId="B25" refString="Lorenz, W, 1998. Systematic List of Extant Ground Beetles of the World. Tutzing, 503 pp." title="Systematic List of Extant Ground Beetles of the World. Tutzing, 503 pp." year="1998">Lorenz (1998)</bibRefCitation>
neither 
<taxonomicName id="18775888D7EE7CF9BDCD0BEB47104C75" genus="B." lsidName="B. parallelipenne" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="parallelipenne">
<emphasis id="070AB915CE35FC92604E46FCC98E1A9E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. parallelipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, nor 
<taxonomicName id="219F0F7A345ED7F49A7527D23A41D7DC" genus="B." lsidName="B. dimidiatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="dimidiatum">
<emphasis id="3F06A3697804912C7FDF16DE07DD2F1A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. dimidiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are reported as belonging to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="ECB80EF21C6E3CBCA7AEB2AB806BCFF6" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion (Actedium)" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Actedium">Bembidion Actedium</taxonomicName>
. From the literature we ascertained that 
<taxonomicName id="0756CD919BD22CAD9B4C943690B70019" genus="B." lsidName="B. dimidiatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="dimidiatum">
<emphasis id="216AE39F3F442A367A505BF0195F4328" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. dimidiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
certainly belongs to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="6C43BAA3C9D8252806205AF9E2C88332" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion (Euperyphus)" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Euperyphus">Bembidion Euperyphus</taxonomicName>
(as currently intended, see above); there still remains uncertainty regarding its precise position, with three (
<taxonomicName id="E6F0F98883475173BB861E31685EFC8D" authority="parallelipenne" genus="B." lsidName="B. parallelipenne subsp. parallelipenne" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="subSpecies" species="parallelipenne" subSpecies="parallelipenne">
<emphasis id="0F4479C5996A44310DA68B64A2925632" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. parallelipenne parallelipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="BE06E288F3D23BEE54FED38ABF7A2713" genus="B." lsidName="B. parallelipenne subsp. exisonum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="subSpecies" species="parallelipenne" subSpecies="exisonum">
<emphasis id="39DF84102F658C756A79765E3E24649B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. parallelipenne exisonum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Lutshnik, 1938, 
<taxonomicName id="512269F64C72DF98393DFA1C52E7BC48" genus="B." lsidName="B. parallelipenne subsp. pseudoripicola" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="subSpecies" species="parallelipenne" subSpecies="pseudoripicola">
<emphasis id="AFCF161854AB6E37A9F81C5A27051EDB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. parallelipenne pseudoripicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Iablokoff-Khnzorian, 1963) taxa currently assigned to the same group. In our opinion it seems unlikely that all the three Caucasian forms could be valid, and it would be necessary to verify them; in any case we suppose that the subspecies more similar to 
<taxonomicName id="66E83ACA007B71314F96B93237054F90" genus="B." lsidName="B. dimidiatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="dimidiatum">
<emphasis id="5984121B8C15CB2355E7ACCF2FC545B0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. dimidiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, mainly due to the elytral coloration, could be 
<taxonomicName id="5884D9E472C7CFE70A91741639755A39" genus="B." lsidName="B. pseudoripicola" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="pseudoripicola">
<emphasis id="E13FEDF68F16AE88412F975062E68B4C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. pseudoripicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; in case of possible synonymies the problem of priority already reported by 
<bibRefCitation id="1043117E53B8175FC714C0770AFCEE0B" author="Netolitzky, F" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Royal Entomological Society of London - Series B: Taxonomy" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" refId="B46" refString="Netolitzky, F, 1943b. Bestimmungs-Tabellen europaeischer Kaefer (9. Stueck). II. Fam. Carabidae, Subfam. Bembidiinae. 66. Gattung: Bembidion Latr. Bestimmungstabelle der Bembidion-Arten des palaearktischen Gebietes. (Mit Hinweisen auf holarktische, aethiopische und orientalische Arten). Koleopterologische Rundschau 29: 1/97-70/166." title="Bestimmungs-Tabellen europaeischer Kaefer (9. Stueck). II. Fam. Carabidae, Subfam. Bembidiinae. 66. Gattung: Bembidion Latr. Bestimmungstabelle der Bembidion-Arten des palaearktischen Gebietes. (Mit Hinweisen auf holarktische, aethiopische und orientalische Arten). Koleopterologische Rundschau 29: 1 / 97 - 70 / 166." year="1943 b">Netolitzky (1943b</bibRefCitation>
: 17/113, note 18) mentioned above should be considered. However 
<taxonomicName id="44457EFB0B23DB6AFEEDA70E746A8C6E" genus="B." lsidName="B. dimidiatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" rank="species" species="dimidiatum">
<emphasis id="693DD3BF6D2363AC9B0BB8B8E22D3696" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="563">B. dimidiatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
must be included in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="1715A278CA89867543855EDEAEECA96C" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bembidion (Euperyphus)" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="563" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Euperyphus">Bembidion Euperyphus</taxonomicName>
as currently intended.
</paragraph>
